The paper deals with image inpainting, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The approach proposed in the paper uses a conditional GAN, which is a popular deep learning technique and falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also introduces constraints on the stochastic component of the GAN, which can be seen as a form of regularization and falls under the category of optimization (cs.GR). Finally, the paper evaluates the approach on several image datasets, which falls under the category of multimedia (cs.MM).
